Package com.olap3.cubeexplorer.mondrian

This is the main entry point for interfacing with mondrian "v3", it handles parsing a config file for the schema and DB connection. It's required to have an open DB connection for this to work due to mondrian's design and the reliance on dimension tables inherent to OLAP cubes. Long term this should be abstracted to a generic data source but this would require an internal schema structure
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CubeUtils
    The main entry point into a specific cube this allows manipulation of member hierarchies, dimensional hierarchy, measures, etc Dirty code relying on capturing internal mondrian structures should be kept here.
    MondrianConfig
    This allows to quickly connect to a mondrian cube using a config file referencing both schema and database connection.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    RolapOnly
    Denotes that a method is only relevant in a ROLAP architecture
